        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "title": "Scrape a fak guard session",
      "description": "How to point Prometheus at a guard session, and where the durable record lives.",
      "type": "text",
      "id": 113,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 54
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {},
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "`fak guard` binds the same gateway `fak serve` does, on a private loopback port that is torn down when the wrapped agent exits \u2014 so to chart a session, pin the port the Prometheus `fak_gateway` job already scrapes:\n\n```\nfak guard --addr 127.0.0.1:8080 -- claude\n```\n\nEvery panel here reads `fak guard`'s live `/metrics`. The durable, hash-chained **decision journal** (`guard-audit.jsonl`, on by default) is the tamper-evident record of the same verdicts \u2014 replay it with `fak audit verify <path>`. Grafana shows the verdicts and savings; it never shows raw request bodies (use `--log FILE` for the structured per-request / per-verdict stream)."
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.5.2"
    }
